UMUAHIA – The Abia State government has procured equipment worth over N65m for the digitalization of the state – owned Broadcasting Corporation of Abia (BCA). Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Information, Elder Ifeanyi Agbai, stated this at a one-day sensitization seminar on Digital Switch Over (DSO), organized by the National Orientation Agency (NOA) in Umuahia, the state capital. While describing the seminar as very timely and in tune with the government’s policies, he pointed out that the state is the first in the country to cue into tele-health initiative by using telecom to drive health care services. In her address, the state Director of NOA, Ngozi Okechukwu, said the areas of coverage of the seminar include process of accessing benefits provided by such policies at the federal, state and local government levels”.